app.non_local_host.body:
FlameChat started with a non-local Ollama address. For privacy reasons it only talks to your own machine (127.0.0.1).

Error: {err}

Fix: unset the OLLAMA_HOST environment variable, or set it to http://127.0.0.1:11434 and restart FlameChat.

attach.unsupported:
“{name}” has a file type FlameChat can't read.

Supported types:
 • Images: {img}
 • Audio: {aud}
 • Text / code: .txt, .md, .json, .yaml, .xml, .html, .csv and most programming source files (.py, .js, .ts, .c/.cpp, .rs, .go, .java, .rb, .sh …)

Convert the file to one of these formats (for instance with Preview / QuickTime / Audacity) and try again.

msg.save_error_body:
FlameChat couldn't write the file.

Usually this means the selected folder is read-only or no longer exists. Pick a different folder (your Desktop or Documents folder is a safe bet) and try again.

Technical details: {err}

ollama.install.launch_failed:
Ollama is installed but wouldn't start.

Technical details: {err}

Try launching Ollama.app manually from your Applications folder (macOS) or Ollama from the Start menu (Windows), then reopen FlameChat.
